  "title": "Vet Nurse",
  "description": "<p>🐾<strong> We’re Hiring: Veterinary Nurse</strong><br>\n<em>Location:</em> Holland Village<br>\n<em>Employment Type:</em> Part / Full-Time</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>About Us</strong><br>\nAt OmniVet, we pride ourselves on providing compassionate, high-quality veterinary care for pets and outstanding support for their owners. Our team is close-knit, supportive, and committed to delivering excellent service — and we’re looking for a <strong>Veterinary Nurse</strong> to join us.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Position Overview</strong><br>\nThe Veterinary Nurse plays a vital role in assisting veterinarians, supporting patients, and ensuring smooth day-to-day operations in the clinic. You’ll be hands-on with patient care, help during procedures, and be a reassuring presence for both pets and their owners.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist veterinarians during consultations, surgeries, and treatments</li>\n  <li>Administer medications, vaccinations, and prescribed treatments</li>\n  <li>Monitor patients pre- and post-surgery</li>\n  <li>Perform diagnostic tests such as bloodwork and urine analysis</li>\n  <li>Educate pet owners on preventive care and post-treatment instructions</li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness and organization of the clinic</li>\n  <li>Ensure accurate and up-to-date medical records</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or certification in Veterinary Nursing (or equivalent)</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in a veterinary clinic is preferred but not essential — fresh graduates welcome</li>\n  <li>Strong teamwork and communication skills</li>\n  <li>Compassion, patience, and attention to detail</li>\n  <li>Willingness to work weekends or evenings on rotation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive salary and staff benefits</li>\n  <li>On-the-job training and continuous learning opportunities</li>\n  <li>Supportive and collaborative work culture</li>\n  <li>Staff discounts on pet care services and products</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br>\nEmail your resume and cover letter to OmniVet.hr@gmail.com with the subject line <strong>\"Application – Veterinary Nurse\"</strong>.</p>\n<p>Join our team and help us provide the best care possible for pets and their families! 🐶🐱</p>",
